Package com.pandora.config.species.services

Interface SpecieStatusService

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractBeanStatusService, DicBeanStatusService, DocBeanStatusService
public interface SpecieStatusService
The SpecieStatusService interface defines methods for checking and toggling the status of biogeochemical species beans in the PANDORA model.

Implementing classes should provide concrete implementations for checking whether a species bean is currently enabled and for toggling its status. The isBeanEnabled() method should return true if the species bean is enabled, and false otherwise. The toggleBeanStatus(boolean) method should toggle the status of the species bean based on the provided parameter, enabling it if currently disabled, or disabling it if currently enabled.

Version:
0.0.1
Author:
Wim Joost van Hoek

    • toggleBeanStatus

      boolean toggleBeanStatus(boolean enabled)
      Toggles the status of the biogeochemical species bean.

      If the species bean is currently enabled, this method will disable it. If it is currently disabled, this method will enable it.

      Parameters:
      enabled - The desired status for the species bean.
      Returns:
      true if the status was successfully toggled, false otherwise.
